# API Contract: {{ display_name }}

This document is the **agreement between the Symfony backend and the Next.js frontend**. Both sides must conform to it. When the contract changes, update this document first, then update the implementation.

> If you are adding a new feature, jump to [Adding a Feature End-to-End](#adding-a-feature-end-to-end).

---

## Base URL

| Environment | Backend URL |
|-------------|-------------|
| Local (Docker) | `http://localhost:8080/api` |
| Local (no Docker) | `http://localhost:8000/api` |
| Staging | `https://api.staging.{{ project_name }}.example.com/api` |
| Production | `https://api.{{ project_name }}.example.com/api` |

The frontend reads `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` from its environment. All service functions in `apps/web/src/services/` prepend this value.

---

## Request Conventions

### Content Type

All requests with a body must send:
```
Content-Type: application/json
```

All requests must accept:
```
Accept: application/json
```

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
For PATCH requests (partial update), use:
```
Content-Type: application/merge-patch+json
```
{% endif %}

{% if use_auth %}
### Authorization

Authenticated endpoints require a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header:

```
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
```

The token is set by the Next.js API route layer (`apps/web/src/app/api/auth/`) and read from an httpOnly cookie. **Client Components never read the raw token.** The `lib/api.ts` utility handles attaching it on the server side.

#### Token Lifecycle

| Event | Action |
|-------|--------|
| Login success | Store `access_token` + `refresh_token` in httpOnly cookies |
| Request with expired token (401) | Attempt silent refresh via `POST /auth/refresh` |
| Refresh success | Update cookies, retry original request |
| Refresh failure | Clear cookies, redirect to `/login` |
| Logout | `POST /auth/logout`, clear cookies |

{% endif %}

