## Error Format

All errors return a consistent JSON body. The frontend's `lib/api.ts` parses this and throws typed errors.

### Error Envelope

```json
{
  "type": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc9110#section-15.5.1",
  "title": "Validation Failed",
  "status": 422,
  "detail": "The request contains invalid data.",
  "violations": [
    {
      "field": "email",
      "message": "This value is not a valid email address."
    },
    {
      "field": "password",
      "message": "This value is too short. It should have 8 characters or more."
    }
  ]
}
```

The `violations` array is present only on 422 responses. For other error types it is omitted.

### Standard HTTP Error Codes

| Code | Meaning | Frontend action |
|------|---------|----------------|
| 400 | Bad Request - malformed JSON | Show generic error toast |
| 401 | Unauthenticated | Attempt token refresh, then redirect to login |
| 403 | Forbidden - wrong role/ownership | Show "Access Denied" message |
| 404 | Not Found | Show 404 page or "not found" inline message |
| 409 | Conflict - duplicate unique field | Map to specific form error |
| 422 | Validation Failed | Map `violations` to form field errors |
| 429 | Rate Limited | Show "too many requests" with retry guidance |
| 500 | Server Error | Show generic error with incident reference |

