## Endpoint Naming Conventions

- All endpoints are prefixed with `/api/`
- Resource names are **plural nouns** in kebab-case: `/api/user-profiles`, not `/api/userProfile`
- Nested resources are allowed one level deep: `/api/users/{id}/addresses`
- Actions that are not CRUD use verbs: `POST /api/users/{id}/deactivate`
- IDs are UUIDs (v7 for new entities): `/api/users/018e7b1a-4a2f-7000-8000-000000000001`

