## Filtering and Search

Collection endpoints that support filtering accept query parameters:

```
GET /api/products?name=widget&status=active&createdAfter=2024-01-01
```

The frontend service function accepts a filter object:

```typescript
export async function getProducts(filters?: {
  name?: string;
  status?: 'active' | 'inactive';
  createdAfter?: string;
  page?: number;
  perPage?: number;
}): Promise<PaginatedResponse<Product>> {
  const params = new URLSearchParams();
  if (filters?.name) params.set('name', filters.name);
  if (filters?.status) params.set('status', filters.status);
  // ...
  return api.get<PaginatedResponse<Product>>(`/products?${params}`);
}
```

